'''Asterby''' is a tiny hamlet squeezed between [[Goulceby]] and [[Scamblesby]], west of [[Louth, Lincolnshire|Louth]], [[Lincolnshire]].  The [[civil parish]] of Asterby had a population of 103 according to the 2001 census.

There is a small church, St Peter.

